Duduzane Zuma has been granted  R100 000 bail at the Specialised Commercial Crimes Court in Johannesburg. He is charged with corruption, allegedly for his role where former deputy Finance Minister Mcebisi Jonas claimed there was an attempt to bribe him at the Guptas’ Saxonwold home in 2015. Jonas alleged in a sworn affidavit to former public protector Thuli Madonsela that he was offered a bribe of R600 million. The former president’s son returned to South Africa on Thursday when he was detained for several hours at the OR Tambo international airport and questioned by the Hawks. Earlier this month, Zuma also received a summons to appear in the Randburg Magistrate’s Court on the 12th of July on two charges of culpable homicide  